title: The Top 10 Hip Hop Singles & Videos Of The Week: Wizkid, Twiztid & Soulja Boy
text:
0 
This past week, Drake and Wizkid link up once again to bring us “Hush Up The Silence.” Horrorcore duo Twiztid drop off their latest single in a DXclusive with “Dead And Gone (Unh-Stop)” and Soulja Boy targets Chris Brown and 50 Cent in his latest diss track, “Hit Em With The Draco.” Wizkid & Drake Are Back With Another Banger 
Wizkid and Drake make great music together, from the “Ojuelegba (Remix)” to their #1 single “One Dance,” to their latest “ Hush Up The Silence .” 
Wizkid’s forthcoming LP Sounds From the Other Side is slated to come out soon. Twiztid Releases Their Next Single 
“Dead And Gone (Unh-Stop)” is Horrorcore duo Twiztid ‘s latest single off their forthcoming album, The Continuous Evilution of Life’s ?’s. 
The Continuous Evilution Of Life’s ?’s is expected to arrive next Friday (January 27). Soulja Boy Hits Chris Brown & 50 Cent With The Draco (Lyrically) 
“Hit Em With The Draco”is Soulja Boy ‘s latest diss track aimed at his nemesis Chris Brown and 50 Cent and comes as the “Crank That” rapper is still promising a boxing match with C-Breezy. 
“Aye 50 Cent what you talking about?/ You made all that money off Vitamin Water and then filed for bankruptcy/ You know I’mma knock Chris Brown out when I see him,” he raps.
